<h2>About GISS</h2>

<h3>Contact GISS</h3>




<p>If you have a question to ask about research or employment at NASA's
Goddard Institute for Space Studies, or about this website,
please consider the following contact options:</p>


<ul>
<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Most research, dataset, and software pages on the GISS website list a specific person
    whom you should contact for further information. Please doublecheck for such info
    before proceeding further.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Media inquiries about GISS research should be addressed to the
    Goddard Space Flight Center
    <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/content/nasa-goddard-guidelines-for-news-media-visits">
    Office of Communications</a>.
    Inquiries regarding Earth science research should be directed to Peter Jacobs.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Scientific questions about the Goddard Institute Surface Temperature Analysis (GISTEMP)
    not answered in the <a href="https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/faq/">FAQ</a>
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/rruedy.html">Dr. Reto A. Ruedy</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Questions about the modelE software resource repository (Simplex)
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/ialeinov.html">Dr. Igor Aleinov</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Inquiries regarding internships and other high school and undergraduate educational
    opportunities not answered on the
    <a href="https://www.giss.nasa.gov/edu/intern/">internship pages</a>
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/mpearce.html">Matthew Pearce</a>.
    If yuo are an educator, please be sure to mention where your school is located.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Questions about graduate study at GISS via Columbia University not addressed
    on the <a href="https://www.giss.nasa.gov/edu/grad/">grad study pages</a>
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/rmiller.html">Dr. Ron Miller</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Inquiries regarding open postdoctoral research opportunities at GISS via Columbia University
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/xhaugh.html">Xiaoming Haugh</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Inquiries regarding mission support (.e.g, programming and IT support)
    employment openings as contractor staff
    should be addressed to <a href="/staff/jbarbara.html">John Barbara</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px" id="Qimageuse">
    Questions about graphics use permissions may be answered in NASA's
    <a href="https://www.nasa.gov/nasa-brand-center/images-and-media/">Images and Media guidelines</a>.
    Per the guidelines there, graphics you may create using a tool on the GISS website do not require
    permission for you to use elsewhere but acknowledgment of their source should be given.
    However, other graphics on the GISS website may be subject to copyright and/or use restrictions;
    please check for an image/graphic credit to determine if so.
    If you need guidance about a particular graphic on the GISS website, contact the GISS
    <a href="mailto:webmaster@giss.nasa.gov">webmaster</a> and be sure to provide
    a specific URL for the page where the graphic is located.</li>
    
    
<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Reports of website problems, from typos on up to server errors, should be sent to the
    GISS <a href="mailto:webmaster@giss.nasa.gov">webmaster</a>.</li>

<li style="margin-left:-24px; margin-bottom:12px">
    Other inquiries may be sent to the GISS
    <a href="mailto:webmaster@giss.nasa.gov">webmaster</a>,
    who will forward the message as appropriate.</li>
</ul>






